m}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|[[Irish Film and Television Awards]]\n| [[7th Irish Film and Television Awards|20 February 2010]]\n| International Film\n!\n| {{nom}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.ifta.ie/iftawinners2010/index.htm |title=Irish Film and Television Academy &#124; IFTA |publisher=Ifta.ie |date=1997-02-26 |accessdate=2011-03-05 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120120143219/http://www.ifta.ie/iftawinners2010/index.htm |archive-date=20 January 2012 |url-status=live |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|[[London Film Critics' Circle Awards]]\n| [[London Film Critics Circle Awards 2009|18 February 2010]]\n| [[London Film Critics' Circle Award for Foreign Language Film of the Year|Foreign Language Film of the Year]]\n| rowspan=\"2\" |  Tomas Alfredson\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"london\">{{cite news|url=http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/8522250.stm|title=Fish Tank hooks four prizes from Critics' Circle|last=Masters|first=Tim|date=19 February 2010|work=BBC News|accessdate=19 February 2010|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100223013922/http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/entertainment/8522250.stm|archive-date=23 February 2010|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|[[NatFilm Festival]]\n| 2008\n| Critics Award\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"natfilm\">{{cite news | url = http://www.arbejderen.dk/index.aspx?F_ID=47658&TS_ID=3&S_ID=41| title = NatFilm Festivalen siger go' nat|last=Strandbeck|first=Mikael | date = 2008-04-09| newspaper =[[Dagbladet Arbejderen]]|language=Danish | accessdate = 2009-04-27 |archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20080525231339/http://www.arbejderen.dk/index.aspx?F_ID=47658&TS_ID=3&S_ID=41 |archivedate = 25 May 2008}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"5\"|[[Online Film Critics Society Awards]]\n| rowspan=\"5\" | [[Online Film Critics Society Awards 2008|19 January 2009]]\n| [[Online Film Critics Society Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n!\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"5\"|<ref name=\"ofcs08\">{{cite web|url=http://ofcs.rottentomatoes.com/pages/awards/2008awards |title=\"WALL-E\" Named Best Picture in Online Film Critics Society Awards |date=2009-01-19 |publisher=[[Online Film Critics Society]] |accessdate=2009-04-05 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090304022251/http://ofcs.rottentomatoes.com/pages/awards/2008awards |archivedate=4 March 2009 }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Online Film Critics Society Award for Best Adapted Screenplay|Best Adapted Screenplay]]\n| John Ajvide Lindqvist\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| [[Online Film Critics Society Award for Best Breakthrough Filmmaker|Breakthrough Filmmaker]]\n| Tomas Alfredson\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" | [[Online Film Critics Society Award for Best Breakthrough Performance|Breakthrough Performance]]\n| Lina Leandersson\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| K\u00e5re Hedebrant\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"2\"|[[Puchon International Fantastic Film Festival]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"| 2009\n| Best Director\n| rowspan=\"2\" |  Tomas Alfredson\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"2\"|<ref name=\"pifan\">{{cite web | url = http://www.fujifilm.com/products/motion_picture/information/0130_01.html | title = Setting out for a record number of awards | date = 2009-01-19 | publisher = [[Fujifilm]] | accessdate = 2010-09-24 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110928152904/http://www.fujifilm.com/products/motion_picture/information/0130_01.html | archive-date = 28 September 2011 | url-status = live | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| Citizen's Choice Award\n| {{won}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |[[San Diego Film Critics Society Awards]]\n| [[San Diego Film Critics Society Awards 2008|15 December 2008]]\n| [[San Diego Film Critics Society Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n!\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"sdfcs\">{{cite web|url=http://sdfcs.org/?p=11 |title=San Diego Film Critics Choose Best of 2008 |date=2008-12-15 |publisher=[[San Diego Film Critics Society]] |accessdate=2009-04-27 |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20110728010501/http://sdfcs.org/2008/12/15/san-diego-film-critics-choose-best-of-2008/ |archivedate=28 July 2011}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|[[San Francisco Film Critics Circle]]\n| [[San Francisco Film Critics Circle Awards 2008|15 December 2008]]\n| [[San Francisco Film Critics Circle Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n!\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"sffcc\">{{cite web|url=http://sffcc.org/2008awards.html |title=2008 San Francisco film critics circle awards |date=2008-12-15 |publisher=[[San Francisco Film Critics Circle]] |accessdate=2009-04-27 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090501065748/http://sffcc.org/2008awards.html |archivedate= 1 May 2009 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"3\"|[[Saturn Award]]s\n| rowspan=\"3\" | [[35th Saturn Awards|25 June 2009]]\n| [[Saturn Award for Best International Film|Best International Film]]\n!\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\" rowspan=\"3\"|<ref name=\"saturn\">{{cite magazine| url = http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118005342.html?categoryid=13&cs=1| title = 'Dark Knight' wins big at Saturns| last = Cohen| first = David S.| date = 2009-06-24| magazine = [[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]| accessdate = 2009-06-25| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090629053442/http://www.variety.com/article/VR1118005342.html?categoryid=13&cs=1| archive-date = 29 June 2009| url-status = live| df = dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"saturn_noms\">{{cite web|url=http://www.saturnawards.org/nominations.html |title=Nominations for the 35th Annual Saturn Awards |last=Olson |first=Dale |date=2009-03-10 |publisher=Academy of Science Fiction, Fantasy & Horror Films |accessdate=2009-03-11 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120221234527/http://www.saturnawards.org/nominations.html |archivedate=21 February 2012 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Performance by a Younger Actor|Best Performance by a Younger Actor]]\n| Lina Leandersson\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| [[Saturn Award for Best Writing|Best Writing]]\n| John Ajvide Lindqvist\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" |[[Sitges Film Festival]]\n| 2008\n| Grand Prize of European Fantasy Film in Gold\n| rowspan=\"2\" |  Tomas Alfredson\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"meliesaward\">{{cite web|url=http://www.melies.org/dorwinners.asp?year=2008 |title=M\u00c9LI\u00c8S D'OR WINNER IN 2008 |publisher=[[European Fantastic Film Festivals Federation]] |accessdate=2009-04-27 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090508061713/http://www.melies.org/dorwinners.asp?year=2008 |archivedate=8 May 2009 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|[[Toronto After Dark Film Festival]]\n| 2008\n| Best Feature Film\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"torontoad\">{{cite web|url=http://torontoafterdark.com/2008/award-winners-2008/ |title=Award Winners 2008 |publisher=[[Toronto After Dark Film Festival]] |accessdate=2009-04-27 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090926185134/http://torontoafterdark.com/2008/award-winners-2008/ |archivedate=26 September 2009 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|[[Toronto Film Critics Association Awards]]\n| [[Toronto Film Critics Association Awards 2008|17 December 2008]]\n| [[Toronto Film Critics Association Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n!\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"tfca\">{{cite web|url=http://torontofilmcritics.com/blog/2008/12/17/tfca-awards-2008/ |title=TFCA Awards 2008 |last=Wilner |first=Norman |date=2008-12-17 |publisher=[[Toronto Film Critics Association]] |accessdate=2009-04-27 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717074852/http://torontofilmcritics.com/blog/2008/12/17/tfca-awards-2008/ |archivedate=17 July 2011 }}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|[[Tribeca Film Festival]]\n| 2008\n| Best Narrative Feature\n| Tomas Alfredson\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"TribecaAward\"/>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|[[Washington DC Area Film Critics Association Awards]]\n| [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Awards 2008|8 December 2008]]\n| [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association Award for Best Foreign Language Film|Best Foreign Language Film]]\n!\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"wafca\">{{cite web| url = http://www.dcfilmcritics.com/awards/| title = WAFCA: Awards \u2013 2008| publisher = [[Washington D.C. Area Film Critics Association]]| accessdate = 2009-04-27| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170312055647/http://www.dcfilmcritics.com/awards/| archive-date = 12 March 2017| url-status = live| df = dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"|[[Woodstock Film Festival]]\n| 2008\n| Best Narrative Feature\n| Tomas Alfredson\n| {{won}}\n|style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref name=\"wff\">{{cite web | url = http://www.woodstockfilmfestival.com/awards2008.htm | title = 2008 Awards info | publisher = [[Woodstock Film Festival]] | accessdate = 2009-04-27 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20081108004602/http://www.woodstockfilmfestival.com/awards2008.htm | archive-date = 8 November 2008 | url-status = live | df = dmy-all }}</ref>\n|}\n\n==American version==\n{{main|Let Me In (film)}}\nAfter the release of ''Let the Right One In'' took place, ''[[Cloverfield]]'' director [[Matt Reeves]] signed on to write and direct an English-language version for [[Overture Films]] and [[Hammer Films]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://movieweb.com/kodi-smit-mcphee-chloe-moretz-and-richard-jenkins-will-let-me-in/|title=Kodi Smit-McPhee, Chloe Moretz and Richard Jenkins Will Let Me In|date=10 January 2009|accessdate=10 January 2009|work=[[MovieWeb]]|first=Brian|last=Gallagher|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171007120010/http://movieweb.com/kodi-smit-mcphee-chloe-moretz-and-richard-jenkins-will-let-me-in/|archive-date=7 October 2017|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Hammer Films acquired the rights at the 2008 Tribeca Film Festival, where ''Let the Right One In'' won the \"Founders Award for Best Narrative Feature\", and Overture films planned to release the film in 2010.<ref name=\"variety_remake\">{{cite web | url = http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117992833.html?categoryid=13&cs=1| title = Matt Reeves bites into 'Right One'|last=Fleming|first=Michael|first2=Dave|last2=McNary|date= 24 September 2008|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]| accessdate = 24 September 2008|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080927081419/http://www.variety.com/article/VR1117992833.html?categoryid=13&cs=1|archivedate=27 September 2008}}</ref> Alfredson has expressed unhappiness about the idea of a remake, saying that \"Remakes should be made of movies that aren't very good, that gives you the chance to fix whatever has gone wrong\" and expressing concern that the end result would be too mainstream.<ref name=\"TA\" /><ref name=\"afremake\">{{cite web| url = http://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/film/article4597816.ab| title = Tr\u00e5kigt med nyinspelning| last = Triches| first = Robert| date = 9 March 2009| work = [[Aftonbladet]]| language = Swedish| accessdate = 2009-04-20| archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20090312074248/http://www.aftonbladet.se/nojesbladet/film/article4597816.ab| archive-date = 12 March 2009| url-status = live| df = dmy-all}}</ref><ref name=\"f\u00f6rst\u00f6ras\">{{cite web|url=http://bloody-disgusting.com/news/13792|title='Let the Right One In' Director Slams Remake|work=Bloody Disgusting|date=30 September 2008|first=Brad|last=Miska|accessdate=30 September 2008|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20081001132630/http://www.bloody-disgusting.com/news/13792|archive-date=1 October 2008|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Alfredson was initially asked to direct the remake, but he turned it down stating that \"I am too old to make the same film twice and I have other stories that I want to tell.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://totalscifionline.com/interviews/3356-tomas-alfredson-new-wave-vampires |title=Tomas Alfredson: New Wave Vampires Interviews \u2013 Total Sci-Fi |publisher=Totalscifionline.com |date=9 April 2009|accessdate=9 April 2009|url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101201235025/http://totalscifionline.com/interviews/3356-tomas-alfredson-new-wave-vampires |archivedate=1 December 2010 |df=dmy-all|first=Calum |last=Waddell}}</ref> Lindqvist, in contrast, said that he had heard that Reeves \"will make a new film based on the book, and not remake the Swedish film\" and so \"it'll be something completely different, but it's going to be really interesting to see.\"<ref name=\"JAL\" /> Hammer Films producer Simon Oakes referred to the project as a remake of the film and later not as a remake, but just as \"Reeves' version\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://collider.com/simon-oakes-interview-let-me-in-hammer-films-ceo-comic-con-the-woman-in-black/|title=Hammer Films CEO Simon Oakes Interview Let Me In; Plus Info on The Woman in Black and Handling the Undead|date=4 August 2010|accessdate=4 August 2010|work=[[Collider (website)|Collider]]|first=Christina|last=Radish|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130702205948/http://collider.com/simon-oakes-interview-let-me-in-hammer-films-ceo-comic-con-the-woman-in-black/|archive-date=2 July 2013|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> ''[[Let Me In (film)|Let Me In]]'' was released in late 2010 starring [[Chlo\u00eb Grace Moretz]] and [[Kodi Smit-McPhee]] as Abby and Owen, Eli's and Oskar's respective counterparts, and received very positive reviews but underperformed at the box office.\n\n==See also==\n* [[Vampire film]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http://www.lettherightoneinmovie.com/}}\n* {{IMDb title|1139797|Let the Right One In}}