|Blancpain GT Series]]''':<br>[[2017 Blancpain GT Series|2017]]: [[Ahmad Al Harthy]] & [[Jonathan Adam]]\n| team titles    = '''[[British GT Championship]]''':<br>[[2016_British_GT_Championship|2016]], [[2017_British_GT_Championship|2017]], [[2018_British_GT_Championship|2018]] (GT3), [[2019_British_GT_Championship|2019]] (GT4)<br />'''[[Michelin Le Mans Cup|Le Mans Cup]]''':<br>[[2017 Michelin Le Mans Cup|2017]]\n}}\n\n'''TF Sport''' is a GT racing team that competes in blue-riband motorsport events throughout Europe including the FIA WEC Super Season and the 24 hours of Le Mans, headed by [[Tom Ferrier]] and supported by [[Aston Martin Racing]].\n\n==Overview==\nFounded in 2014 by former British Touring Car and British GT driver, Tom Ferrier, TF Sport dovetailed a third British GT campaign with a strong European competition programme in the newly established GT3 Le Mans Cup and International GT Open.\n\nHaving successfully competed on 2015 in the [[2015 Blancpain GT Series|Blancpain Series]], the [[GT cup]]<ref>{{cite news|title=GT CUP TITLE WITHIN PAUL BAILEY AND ANDY SCHULZ'S REACH AT DONINGTON PARK|url=http://tfsport.co.uk/news/gt-cup-title-within-paul-bailey-and-andy-schulzs-reach-donington-park|date=16 September 2015}}</ref> and the [[2015 International GT Open|International GT Open]], TF Sport has launched an additional campaign for the [[2016 GT3 Le Mans Cup|Michelin GT3 Le Mans Cup]] title in the 2016 season.<ref>{{cite news|title=TF Sport welcomes back Devon Modell and Andrew Jarman for 'Road to Le Mans'|url=http://www.gt3lemanscup.com/en/news/tf-sport-welcomes-back-devon-modell-and-andrew-jarman-for-road-to-le-mans/64}}</ref>\n\nChampionship titles at home and abroad turned 2016 into a breakthrough year for TF Sport, but 2017 promises to be even more momentous, as the official Aston Martin Racing Partner Team is set to step over to GTE-spec machinery for a dream assault on the European Le Mans Series and the legendary 24 Hours of Le Mans.<ref>{{cite news|title=ASTON MARTIN RACING SET FOR 24 HOURS OF LE MANS FIGHT|url=https://media.astonmartin.com/aston-martin-racing-set-for-24-hours-of-le-mans-fight/}}</ref>\n\n{{Clear}}\n\n==British GT results==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%; width:750px\"\n! colspan=9| [[British GT Championship|British GT]] results\n|-\n! Year\n! Car\n! Class\n! Drivers\n! Wins\n! Podiums\n! Points\n! {{H:title|Drivers Championship|D.C.}}\n! {{H:title|Teams Championship|T.C.}}\n|-\n| rowspan=1| [[2014 British GT season|2014]]\n| rowspan=1| [[Aston Martin V8 Vantage GT4]]<br>\n| rowspan=1 align=\"center\"| GT4\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} Andrew Jarman<br>{{flagicon|GBR}} Devon Modell\n| 2\n| 7\n| 190\n| style=\"background:silver;\"|2nd\n| rowspan=1 style=\"background:#FFDF9F;\"|3rd\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[2015 British GT season|2015]]\n| rowspan=2| [[Aston Martin Vantage (2005)|Aston Martin V12 Vantage GT3]]<br>\n| rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| GT3\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} Andrew Jarman<br>{{flagicon|GBR}} Jody Fannin\n| 0\n| 2\n| 60\n| 7th\n| rowspan=2 style=\"background:#FFDF9F;\"|3rd\n|-\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} Matt Bell<br>{{flagicon|GBR}} Derek Johnston\n| 1\n| 3\n| 107\n| 5th\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[2016 British GT season|2016]]\n| rowspan=2| [[Aston Martin Vantage (2005)|Aston Martin V12 Vantage GT3]]<br>\n| rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| GT3\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} Jonathan Adam<br>{{flagicon|GBR}} Derek Johnston\n| 2\n| 2\n| 106\n| style=\"background:#FFFFBF;\"|1st\n| rowspan=2 style=\"background:#FFFFBF;\"|1st\n|-\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} John Barnes<br>{{flagicon|GBR}} Mark Farmer\n| 1\n| 1\n| 79.5\n| 5th\n|-\n| rowspan=2| [[2017 British GT season|2017]]\n| rowspan=2| [[Aston Martin Vantage (2005)|Aston Martin V12 Vantage GT3]]<br>\n| rowspan=2 align=\"center\"| GT3\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} Jonathan Adam<br>{{flagicon|GBR}} Derek Johnston\n| 2\n| 4\n| 142.5\n| style=\"background:#FFDF9F;\"|3st\n| rowspan=2 style=\"background:#FFFFBF;\"|1st\n|-\n| {{flagicon|GBR}} John Barnes<br>{{flagicon|GBR}} Mark Farmer\n| 0\n|